00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,180
Minawar's fiance is here
to pick her up again.

288
00:15:24,180 --> 00:15:25,540
So beautiful.

289
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:27,810
Today, they're even treating us
to a whole roasted lamb.

290
00:15:27,810 --> 00:15:29,120
You're so pretty.

291
00:15:37,850 --> 00:15:39,090
I want to go take a picture with her.

292
00:15:39,090 --> 00:15:40,440
You go. I'm an introvert.

293
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,680
Come, come, come.

294
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:42,200
Go.

295
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,060
Thank you, Grandma.

296
00:15:43,060 --> 00:15:44,280
Wait a moment.

297
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:48,360
I told you
she doesn't want to take a picture.

298
00:15:53,470 --> 00:15:55,160
Thank you, Grandma.

299
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:56,200
Let's go.

300
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:18,450
My little pigeon has flown back.

301
00:16:19,040 --> 00:16:20,210
Grandma.

302
00:16:24,660 --> 00:16:26,250
I'm back.

303
00:16:33,590 --> 00:16:34,900
Will it survive?

304
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:36,010
It will.

305
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:38,090
There should still be a chance.

306
00:16:38,090 --> 00:16:39,350
I think it'll survive.

307
00:16:40,090 --> 00:16:42,440
A fig can grow in a palace's flowerpot,

308
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:44,490
but it can also grow
in the farmer's field.

309
00:16:44,490 --> 00:16:46,350
Arzugul, soak it in water.

310
00:16:44,810 --> 00:16:46,440
[Arzugul, Arzugul’s nickname]

311
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:47,780
I'll go home and get a pot.

312
00:16:47,870 --> 00:16:48,400
Go ahead.

313
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:03,370
Um,

314
00:17:04,089 --> 00:17:05,180
excuse me,

315
00:17:05,180 --> 00:17:07,050
is this the Camel Bell Inn?

316
00:17:07,180 --> 00:17:08,420
Yes, this is my home.

317
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,510
Dad, we have a guest.

318
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:21,470
Hello, I...

319
00:17:21,470 --> 00:17:22,290
Young man,

320
00:17:23,270 --> 00:17:24,740
what are you

321
00:17:24,849 --> 00:17:26,200
looking around for?

322
00:17:26,859 --> 00:17:29,140
Are you here to stay at our inn?

323
00:17:29,370 --> 00:17:31,980
Yes, sir. Your place is so hard to find.

324
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,210
Several people said that way,

325
00:17:34,210 --> 00:17:35,290
but they all said differently.

326
00:17:35,290 --> 00:17:36,890
If we Kashgar people tell you

327
00:17:37,510 --> 00:17:38,440
it's over there,

328
00:17:38,620 --> 00:17:40,620
you'll have to walk for ten minutes.

329
00:17:40,790 --> 00:17:42,010
If they say

330
00:17:42,010 --> 00:17:43,530
it's over there,

331
00:17:43,530 --> 00:17:45,730
you'll have to walk for thirty minutes.

332
00:17:45,790 --> 00:17:48,160
That's Kashgar's sense of humor.

333
00:17:49,140 --> 00:17:51,550
According to the internet, your guesthouse

334
00:17:51,550 --> 00:17:52,810
is the oldest in all of Kashgar, right?

335
00:17:52,810 --> 00:17:55,340
I wouldn't call it the oldest.

336
00:17:55,990 --> 00:17:56,660
But

337
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:58,710
the deed for our house

338
00:17:59,010 --> 00:18:00,380
is written on sheepskin.

339
00:18:00,380 --> 00:18:01,160
See this?

340
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,900
This pillar in our house

341
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:04,530
is over a hundred years old

342
00:18:04,530 --> 00:18:05,900
and still in great shape.

343
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:06,440
This pillar

344
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:08,470
was specially made from apricot wood.

345
00:18:08,470 --> 00:18:09,640
A hundred years from now,

346
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:11,750
it'll still be like this, perfectly fine.

347
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:13,010
This is pretty good.

348
00:18:13,010 --> 00:18:14,750
The location of your inn

349
00:18:14,750 --> 00:18:16,010
is really hard to find.

350
00:18:16,640 --> 00:18:17,920
Even in peak season, no need to book.

351
00:18:17,920 --> 00:18:19,180
There are still rooms.

352
00:18:19,790 --> 00:18:21,450
It seems Kashgar doesn't have

353
00:18:21,620 --> 00:18:22,730
that many tourists.

354
00:18:22,730 --> 00:18:23,770
Young man.

355
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:25,900
They are the only ones with rooms left.

356
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:26,960
The rest

357
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:27,860
are all full.

358
00:18:27,860 --> 00:18:29,180
Go, go, go.

359
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:32,290
Young man.

360
00:18:33,290 --> 00:18:36,290
Sorry, we're not open today.

361
00:18:36,290 --> 00:18:38,490
We're not taking any new guests.

362
00:18:38,820 --> 00:18:40,620
Hey, isn't that girl a guest?

363
00:18:41,210 --> 00:18:42,620
Why can she stay here?

364
00:18:43,380 --> 00:18:44,770
She's our child.

365
00:18:44,770 --> 00:18:47,310
She's my best friend Xia Hui's daughter.

366
00:18:58,550 --> 00:18:59,470
Friend,

367
00:18:59,470 --> 00:19:01,640
if you insist on staying at our inn today,

368
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:03,040
there's nothing I can do.

369
00:19:03,270 --> 00:19:03,860
But we're having

370
00:19:03,860 --> 00:19:05,770
a Meshrep tonight.

371
00:19:05,770 --> 00:19:07,420
I'm afraid of disturbing you,

372
00:19:07,420 --> 00:19:08,200
you know?

373
00:19:08,790 --> 00:19:09,440
Sir,

374
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:12,470
what's a Meshrep?

375
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:14,140
You don't even know

376
00:19:14,140 --> 00:19:15,140
what a Meshrep is?

377
00:19:15,550 --> 00:19:16,360
A Meshrep

378
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:17,290
is just about all of us

379
00:19:17,290 --> 00:19:18,810
getting together,

380
00:19:18,810 --> 00:19:20,270
eating,

381
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:21,500
drinking tea,

382
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:23,440
and having a good time.

383
00:19:26,210 --> 00:19:27,120
But today,

384
00:19:27,120 --> 00:19:28,310
this Meshrep

385
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:30,750
is a bit special.

386
00:19:30,970 --> 00:19:31,970
Especially good?

387
00:19:33,620 --> 00:19:34,380
Friend.

388
00:19:37,490 --> 00:19:38,440
Our neighbor,

389
00:19:38,440 --> 00:19:39,960
this meatbun, loves here.

390
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:40,700
Look! Ha!

391
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:42,560
Get some good rest, young man.

392
00:19:42,590 --> 00:19:43,520
Come down later.

393
00:19:50,140 --> 00:19:50,900
Laili,

394
00:19:51,070 --> 00:19:52,680
call my daughter

395
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:53,810
and see where she is.

396
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:00,550
Hurry.

397
00:20:01,510 --> 00:20:02,440
Come here.

398
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:03,650
I'm leaving.

399
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:05,070
Okay.

400
00:20:07,460 --> 00:20:08,770
I'll pick you up tomorrow.

401
00:20:08,770 --> 00:20:09,840
Hurry. Hurry. Hurry.

402
00:20:09,840 --> 00:20:11,100
Your dad is angry.

403
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:13,000
Dad, I'm back.

404
00:20:13,140 --> 00:20:14,030
You're back.

405
00:20:14,030 --> 00:20:14,810
I'm back.

406
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:18,700
Arzugul.

407
00:20:20,380 --> 00:20:21,110
You're back.

408
00:20:22,620 --> 00:20:23,470
-Alimu.
-Dad.

409
00:20:23,470 --> 00:20:24,200
Uncle.

410
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:25,750
Alimu is here.

411
00:20:26,030 --> 00:20:26,790
Laili.

412
00:20:29,290 --> 00:20:29,960
Is this

413
00:20:30,380 --> 00:20:31,270
Arzugul?

414
00:20:31,550 --> 00:20:32,950
How did you get so pretty?

415
00:20:33,860 --> 00:20:35,190
Was I not pretty before?

416
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:36,700
No, no, no.

417
00:20:37,010 --> 00:20:38,790
You are just pretty.

418
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:40,420
But some people

419
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:41,990
are not only pretty,

420
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:43,180
but also know how to manipulate others.

421
00:20:43,180 --> 00:20:44,180
How have I manipulated others?

422
00:20:44,180 --> 00:20:45,080
Don't you know?

423
00:20:45,180 --> 00:20:46,550
Thank you, Alimu.

424
00:20:46,550 --> 00:20:48,550
Didn't your brother say
he'd be back these days?

425
00:20:48,550 --> 00:20:49,810
Why haven't I seen him?

426
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:51,710
You're still thinking about my brother?

427
00:20:51,710 --> 00:20:53,530
He works hard enough driving out there.

428
00:20:53,530 --> 00:20:56,030
He even went out of his way
to buy you handmade chocolates.

429
00:20:56,030 --> 00:20:58,760
Minawar,
if you're not interested in my brother,

430
00:20:58,890 --> 00:21:00,640
then don't let him run errands for you,

431
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:01,140
okay?

432
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:03,310
You haven't changed a bit.

433
00:21:03,310 --> 00:21:04,490
Still so sharp-tongued, huh?

434
00:21:04,490 --> 00:21:05,340
Go.

435
00:21:08,290 --> 00:21:09,200
Arzugul.

436
00:21:10,790 --> 00:21:11,600
I want to eat too.

437
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:12,100
You eat.

438
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:13,180
Minawar.

439
00:21:13,810 --> 00:21:15,990
Laili said you went out to the countryside
to perform.

440
00:21:15,990 --> 00:21:16,790
Are you tired?

441
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:18,660
How could I be tired?

442
00:21:18,660 --> 00:21:20,470
My boyfriend bought a new car.

443
00:21:20,470 --> 00:21:21,730
He drives me every day.

444
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:22,750
However, some people

445
00:21:22,750 --> 00:21:24,440
didn't even come out to meet us.

446
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:25,900
Arzugul went off to do her thing.

447
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:26,840
Is it confirmed?

448
00:21:27,070 --> 00:21:28,440
If you are sure he's the one,

449
00:21:28,440 --> 00:21:29,530
it's not too late to meet.

450
00:21:29,530 --> 00:21:30,790
They're getting engaged.

451
00:21:30,790 --> 00:21:33,070
People coming back from Shanghai
are indeed different.

452
00:21:33,070 --> 00:21:34,380
You've gotten so full of yourself.

453
00:21:34,380 --> 00:21:36,730
You didn't even bother
to call me on my birthday.

454
00:21:36,730 --> 00:21:37,350
Laili,

455
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:38,520
come here.

456
00:21:39,010 --> 00:21:39,670
Let's chat.

457
00:21:43,710 --> 00:21:44,840
Come, sit closer.

458
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,770
I came all the way back from Shanghai,

459
00:21:47,770 --> 00:21:48,660
you didn't even come to pick me up.

460
00:21:48,660 --> 00:21:49,730
But you expected me to go and meet you?

461
00:21:49,730 --> 00:21:52,010
There was a situation.

462
00:21:52,010 --> 00:21:52,970
A situation?

463
00:21:52,970 --> 00:21:55,430
A boyfriend matters more
than a best friend.

464
00:21:59,730 --> 00:22:01,560
Arzugul, eat more.

465
00:22:01,580 --> 00:22:02,550
Okay.

466
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:04,490
Thank you, Grandma.

467
00:22:07,430 --> 00:22:09,530
Arzugul, since you came back this time,

468
00:22:09,530 --> 00:22:11,050
can you stay for a few more days?

469
00:22:11,050 --> 00:22:12,070
I'm not sure yet.

470
00:22:12,070 --> 00:22:12,990
I don't have much time off,

471
00:22:12,990 --> 00:22:14,420
so I might go back after I'm done.

472
00:22:14,420 --> 00:22:15,050
That fast?

473
00:22:15,550 --> 00:22:16,990
You haven't changed much.

474
00:22:16,990 --> 00:22:17,840
Dad.

475
00:22:17,840 --> 00:22:19,190
It's been less than a year

476
00:22:19,190 --> 00:22:20,120
since Arzugul last came back.

477
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:21,380
What could have changed?

478
00:22:21,380 --> 00:22:22,620
Arzugul is now a manager

479
00:22:22,620 --> 00:22:25,250
at a big company in Shanghai.

480
00:22:26,340 --> 00:22:27,120
What manager?

481
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:27,880
I am just working

482
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:29,380
for someone else.

483
00:22:29,380 --> 00:22:31,400
Not all jobs are the same.

484
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,660
Xia Zi

485
00:22:32,660 --> 00:22:34,770
is a director

486
00:22:34,770 --> 00:22:36,250
at a real estate company in Shanghai.

487
00:22:36,250 --> 00:22:38,660
Turns out my granddaughter is amazing.

488
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:40,720
My daughter, Laili, told me that

489
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:43,200
Arzugul even bought a house in Shanghai.

490
00:22:43,490 --> 00:22:45,820
It's not a big house.

491
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:47,990
Back in the day,

492
00:22:47,990 --> 00:22:49,730
Arzugul's parents

493
00:22:49,730 --> 00:22:50,730
were very busy.

494
00:22:50,730 --> 00:22:52,460
I raised her single-handedly.

495
00:22:52,970 --> 00:22:53,640
As you know,

496
00:22:53,640 --> 00:22:54,900
I used to build houses.

497
00:22:55,290 --> 00:22:56,660
This guest room on the second floor,

498
00:22:56,660 --> 00:22:57,770
I built it myself.

499
00:22:57,770 --> 00:22:58,960
When I was building this house,

500
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:00,230
I was mixing cement over there,

501
00:23:00,230 --> 00:23:02,010
and Arzugul was sitting beside me,

502
00:23:02,010 --> 00:23:04,290
playing with mud.

503
00:23:04,970 --> 00:23:06,730
The little camel knows the way

504
00:23:07,050 --> 00:23:09,880
only because the old camel led it well.

505
00:23:10,140 --> 00:23:12,050
Camels are camels, alpacas are alpacas.

506
00:23:12,050 --> 00:23:13,420
They just look alike.

507
00:23:13,420 --> 00:23:16,460
Arzugul is an architectural designer.

508
00:23:16,460 --> 00:23:18,160
You are just a construction worker.
It's different.

509
00:23:18,160 --> 00:23:19,470
How can it be the same?

510
00:23:20,770 --> 00:23:23,030
Later, when Arzugul takes you to Shanghai

511
00:23:23,030 --> 00:23:25,420
to see the skyscrapers she built,

512
00:23:25,420 --> 00:23:26,550
you will know.

513
00:23:28,900 --> 00:23:29,920
That's true.

514
00:23:30,470 --> 00:23:31,400
Arzugul has been

515
00:23:31,730 --> 00:23:34,120
top of her class since she was young.

516
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:36,380
She is very smart and always comes first.

517
00:25:11,770 --> 00:25:14,290
Too bad the moon is hiding tonight.

518
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:21,920
They are here.

519
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:23,400
Here.

520
00:26:38,090 --> 00:26:39,610
I brought your dad back.

521
00:26:40,450 --> 00:26:41,400
Don't be too sad.

522
00:26:42,230 --> 00:26:43,960
Your dad would be heartbroken.

523
00:26:59,440 --> 00:27:00,120
Go inside.

524
00:27:01,940 --> 00:27:02,680
Come in.

525
00:27:09,070 --> 00:27:10,710
We are gathered here today

526
00:27:11,990 --> 00:27:13,640
to say goodbye to our

527
00:27:14,100 --> 00:27:15,010
good brother

528
00:27:15,840 --> 00:27:16,770
and good friend,

529
00:27:17,030 --> 00:27:17,900
Xia Hui.

530
00:27:18,530 --> 00:27:20,600
He was serving as a foreign aid doctor

531
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:22,550
when he encountered local conflict

532
00:27:22,550 --> 00:27:24,010
and was tragically killed

533
00:27:24,010 --> 00:27:25,140
in an explosion.

534
00:27:25,850 --> 00:27:26,920
It has been over half a year

535
00:27:26,920 --> 00:27:28,270
since he passed away.

536
00:27:29,210 --> 00:27:30,340
Our sister-in-law,

537
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:31,370
Chang Yue,

538
00:27:31,900 --> 00:27:33,420
brought him back home.

539
00:27:36,750 --> 00:27:37,680
Let's talk about

540
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:40,730
the beautiful memories

541
00:27:41,180 --> 00:27:42,640
Xia Hui left for each of us.

542
00:27:47,570 --> 00:27:48,640
The last time Hui

543
00:27:50,120 --> 00:27:52,270
called me,

544
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:55,390
he said he would be back in half a year.

545
00:27:55,410 --> 00:27:58,430
He told me to take care of my health

546
00:27:58,460 --> 00:28:00,900
and take my medicine on time every day.

547
00:28:01,270 --> 00:28:04,070
He also specifically asked Yue

548
00:28:04,570 --> 00:28:06,470
to give me this watch.

549
00:28:06,940 --> 00:28:09,010
Whenever I think of Hui,

550
00:28:09,080 --> 00:28:11,040
I feel very sad.

551
00:28:12,020 --> 00:28:14,380
The last time Uncle Xia contacted me

552
00:28:14,940 --> 00:28:16,620
was about a year ago.

553
00:28:17,530 --> 00:28:19,790
He suddenly called me and

554
00:28:20,270 --> 00:28:22,250
praised my performance.

555
00:28:22,900 --> 00:28:25,960
Then he bought twenty tickets

556
00:28:25,960 --> 00:28:27,560
and gave them to his friends.

557
00:28:28,460 --> 00:28:30,390
I used to chat with Uncle Xia often.

558
00:28:31,290 --> 00:28:32,290
He asked me

559
00:28:32,510 --> 00:28:34,440
how to add effects to short videos.

560
00:28:35,130 --> 00:28:37,790
He even said
he wanted to create his own account.

561
00:28:44,250 --> 00:28:45,070
Xia.

562
00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:47,880
The last thing he said to me

563
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:49,970
were in a comment on my social media.

564
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:53,660
He posted, "These flowers finally bloomed,

565
00:28:53,660 --> 00:28:54,900
congratulations!

566
00:28:55,360 --> 00:28:57,420
It's almost as beautiful as my wife."

567
00:29:01,660 --> 00:29:04,510
The last time Xia Hui called me,

568
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:06,340
he said,

569
00:29:06,550 --> 00:29:07,200
"Brother,

570
00:29:07,200 --> 00:29:09,180
I eat bread every day here.

571
00:29:10,270 --> 00:29:13,010
I really miss our thin-skinned buns.”

572
00:29:14,900 --> 00:29:17,010
When Xia Hui called me,

573
00:29:17,010 --> 00:29:18,050
he said,

574
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:18,990
"Nur,

575
00:29:19,420 --> 00:29:21,400
don't forget you have high blood pressure.

576
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:24,900
You must take care of your health.

577
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:26,250
Eat less greasy food,

578
00:29:26,250 --> 00:29:28,250
and don't overexert yourself."

579
00:29:28,250 --> 00:29:29,990
That's what he told me.

580
00:29:33,320 --> 00:29:36,240
♪My longed-for lover♪

581
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:47,500
♪May you live a thousand years♪

582
00:29:49,370 --> 00:29:57,840
♪Lift your veil and let me see♪

583
00:29:54,850 --> 00:29:56,420
Everyone, stop crying.

584
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:57,370
Don't cry.

585
00:29:57,840 --> 00:29:58,510
We

586
00:29:58,180 --> 00:30:05,640
♪Your flower-like smile♪

587
00:29:58,510 --> 00:30:00,160
can't let Xia laugh at us.

588
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:02,360
Let's sing.

589
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:03,360
Sing.

590
00:30:03,360 --> 00:30:05,570
Xia would want us to live happily.

591
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:13,500
♪Since the moment I saw you, my love♪

592
00:30:13,530 --> 00:30:21,210
♪I've fallen into the pit of worries♪

593
00:30:21,350 --> 00:30:25,180
♪Oh dear love♪

594
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:29,320
♪Where could there be a flower like you?♪

595
00:30:29,350 --> 00:30:36,680
♪A lover with eyes that burn like fire♪

596
00:30:36,750 --> 00:30:48,060
♪Oh, my love♪

597
00:30:48,350 --> 00:30:51,780
♪A lover with eyes that burn like fire♪

598
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:56,210
Wang,

599
00:30:56,460 --> 00:30:58,230
hurry up and show me your guesthouse.

600
00:30:58,230 --> 00:30:58,620
Anyway,

601
00:30:58,620 --> 00:31:01,020
we've already signed the contract, right?

602
00:31:01,180 --> 00:31:03,290
Your taste is absolutely fine.

603
00:31:03,290 --> 00:31:05,180
I trust you 100%.

604
00:31:07,810 --> 00:31:08,600
Hello.

605
00:31:09,840 --> 00:31:10,380
Ms. Xia.

606
00:31:10,420 --> 00:31:10,920
Did you get

607
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:12,120
a notice from HR?

608
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:13,920
What notice?

609
00:31:15,140 --> 00:31:17,230
Wasn't there a rumor about layoffs before?

610
00:31:17,230 --> 00:31:18,760
Right after you took leave,

611
00:31:18,790 --> 00:31:19,590
HR started calling people

612
00:31:19,590 --> 00:31:21,250
from our team for interviews.

613
00:31:21,420 --> 00:31:22,920
They are using your absence

614
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:23,750
to target us.

615
00:31:24,730 --> 00:31:26,030
I've already been interviewed.

616
00:31:26,030 --> 00:31:28,030
I feel like they'll talk to you soon.

617
00:31:29,100 --> 00:31:29,910
Wait for me.

618
00:31:29,970 --> 00:31:32,700
I'll go back
as soon as I finish the family business.

619
00:31:32,700 --> 00:31:33,620
No.

620
00:31:33,620 --> 00:31:34,700
When the property market was so good,

621
00:31:34,700 --> 00:31:36,290
we made them so much money.

622
00:31:36,550 --> 00:31:37,340
Now that the market is bad,

623
00:31:37,340 --> 00:31:38,740
they just want to fire us.

624
00:31:38,920 --> 00:31:41,070
Ms. Xia, you should make plans early too.

625
00:31:41,070 --> 00:31:42,840
What plans can I make?

626
00:31:42,840 --> 00:31:43,710
Now that I've lost my job,

627
00:31:43,710 --> 00:31:45,290
who's going to pay my mortgage?

628
00:31:45,290 --> 00:31:46,160
Don't worry.

629
00:31:46,790 --> 00:31:47,750
I've got some things to take care of,

630
00:31:47,750 --> 00:31:49,150
so I'll talk to you later.

631
00:32:02,510 --> 00:32:03,360
Uh,

632
00:32:05,080 --> 00:32:06,640
w-what a coincidence.

633
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:09,980
Sorry, I don't want to talk right now.

634
00:32:11,470 --> 00:32:12,530
M-My condolences.

635
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:17,320
I didn't mean

636
00:32:17,460 --> 00:32:19,170
the layoff thing earlier.

637
00:32:19,170 --> 00:32:20,340
I meant...

638
00:32:20,340 --> 00:32:22,340
tonight, about that black box,

639
00:32:22,340 --> 00:32:23,680
y-your dad...

640
00:32:50,730 --> 00:32:52,510
The thin-skinned buns.

641
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:56,960
I'll learn how to make them someday.

642
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:58,490
Then I'll make them for you.

643
00:33:07,100 --> 00:33:11,310
[2014]

644
00:33:07,680 --> 00:33:08,880
My dear wife is here.

645
00:33:08,900 --> 00:33:10,560
Do you have any instructions?

646
00:33:17,700 --> 00:33:18,830
Teach me how to ride.

647
00:33:20,990 --> 00:33:22,590
When you're working abroad,

648
00:33:22,620 --> 00:33:23,880
I might need it.

649
00:33:26,100 --> 00:33:27,230
My dear wife, you...

650
00:33:27,710 --> 00:33:28,360
So,

651
00:33:28,850 --> 00:33:30,110
you agreed to let me go?

652
00:33:31,660 --> 00:33:32,640
You supported me

653
00:33:33,230 --> 00:33:34,960
working in Xinjiang back then.

654
00:33:35,010 --> 00:33:37,140
Now it's my turn to support your dream.

655
00:33:50,860 --> 00:33:53,310
Just don't come back
missing an arm or a leg.

656
00:33:53,810 --> 00:33:55,810
Otherwise, I won't take care of you.

657
00:33:58,440 --> 00:33:59,290
I promise.

658
00:34:26,080 --> 00:34:28,250
Mom, how about I move back in with you?

659
00:34:29,820 --> 00:34:31,510
You finally come back.

660
00:34:31,820 --> 00:34:33,480
Spend more time with Grandma.

661
00:35:14,460 --> 00:35:15,510
Grandma.

662
00:35:19,380 --> 00:35:20,570
Grandma.

663
00:35:22,490 --> 00:35:23,380
Tell me,

664
00:35:24,780 --> 00:35:25,780
why is life so hard

665
00:35:26,110 --> 00:35:29,110
when you grow up?

666
00:35:31,220 --> 00:35:32,220
Granddaughter.

667
00:35:32,990 --> 00:35:37,690
The sun of Kashgar lights up
a thousand roads,

668
00:35:38,380 --> 00:35:43,050
and your shadow will tell you
which one to take.

669
00:35:51,190 --> 00:35:52,110
You silly girl,

670
00:35:52,140 --> 00:35:55,310
are you trying to break my old bones?

671
00:35:59,030 --> 00:36:00,880
Grandma.

672
00:36:03,550 --> 00:36:05,840
Don't eat so many chickpeas.

673
00:37:31,550 --> 00:37:32,130
Zi.

674
00:37:33,670 --> 00:37:35,530
Today is your first day of school.

675
00:37:35,900 --> 00:37:37,030
When you get to school,

676
00:37:37,030 --> 00:37:38,860
don't ever fight with your classmates.

677
00:37:38,860 --> 00:37:39,320
Okay.

678
00:37:40,190 --> 00:37:42,470
Just because you are the boss at the inn

679
00:37:42,820 --> 00:37:44,280
doesn't mean you'll be the same at school.

680
00:37:44,280 --> 00:37:46,150
Those boys out there are wild.

681
00:37:59,030 --> 00:37:59,860
Dad.

682
00:38:01,030 --> 00:38:02,220
Hurry up, Zi.

683
00:38:06,030 --> 00:38:06,940
Did you miss me?

684
00:38:06,940 --> 00:38:07,650
I did.

685
00:38:08,240 --> 00:38:09,820
Are you enjoying your first day at school?

686
00:38:09,820 --> 00:38:10,440
I am.

687
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:13,470
Dad.

688
00:38:15,710 --> 00:38:17,570
You used to wait for me to come home

689
00:38:18,570 --> 00:38:21,090
under that big tree,
through rain or wind.

690
00:38:22,630 --> 00:38:24,570
You hoped I could be a little dove

691
00:38:25,100 --> 00:38:26,310
flying freely.

692
00:38:29,030 --> 00:38:29,880
I'm sorry.

693
00:38:31,090 --> 00:38:32,460
I let you down.

694
00:38:34,260 --> 00:38:35,010
Now,

695
00:38:36,510 --> 00:38:38,220
you'll never wait for me

696
00:38:38,220 --> 00:38:39,680
under that big tree again.

697
00:38:44,220 --> 00:38:46,280
This time, returning to my hometown,

698
00:38:46,630 --> 00:38:48,030
where will Satar's music

699
00:38:49,380 --> 00:38:51,010
take me?

700
00:39:29,130 --> 00:39:31,690
Welcome aboard Bus 943,

701
00:39:31,690 --> 00:39:33,860
bound for Pu'an Road, Yan'an East Road.

702
00:39:33,860 --> 00:39:36,320
Welcome aboard Bus 943,

703
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:37,660
[Shanghai 7 months ago]

704
00:39:36,320 --> 00:39:38,760
bound for Pu'an Road, Yan'an East Road.

705
00:39:40,460 --> 00:39:42,340
Everyone, thank you for
continuing to follow

706
00:39:42,340 --> 00:39:44,000
our homeowners' live stream.

707
00:39:44,070 --> 00:39:45,320
The Rose Garden housing project

708
00:39:45,320 --> 00:39:46,720
has been suspended for two months,

709
00:39:46,720 --> 00:39:49,320
yet we are still
paying our mortgages as usual.

710
00:39:49,420 --> 00:39:50,990
I want to ask when the developer

711
00:39:50,990 --> 00:39:52,970
will give us an explanation.

712
00:39:52,970 --> 00:39:53,960
The longer this goes on,

713
00:39:53,960 --> 00:39:55,970
the more disappointed we become.

714
00:40:04,970 --> 00:40:05,610
Zi.

715
00:40:05,820 --> 00:40:06,530
Dad.

716
00:40:07,380 --> 00:40:08,130
Zi.

717
00:40:09,740 --> 00:40:12,140
Did you go to Huaqiao
to see the house again?

718
00:40:12,220 --> 00:40:14,670
Isn't it just six months
until the handover?

719
00:40:14,670 --> 00:40:15,380
Dad.

720
00:40:16,170 --> 00:40:18,220
Well, about the house...

721
00:40:18,590 --> 00:40:18,990
What?

722
00:40:19,130 --> 00:40:19,530
No, no.

723
00:40:19,530 --> 00:40:21,130
It's lagging. It's lagging.

724
00:40:21,740 --> 00:40:22,670
What did you say?

725
00:40:23,840 --> 00:40:26,040
I didn't hear you. What did you just say?

726
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:26,900
Well,

727
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:29,650
I called to tell you something important.

728
00:40:30,580 --> 00:40:31,100
You,

729
00:40:31,300 --> 00:40:32,960
take a look at your own WeChat Moments.

730
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:34,320
Okay, I'll hang up first.

731
00:40:34,320 --> 00:40:35,460
I'll go take a look.

732
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:55,380
I knew you couldn't sleep.

733
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:57,210
We're here to keep you company.

734
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:08,190
Cry if you want to.

735
00:41:08,190 --> 00:41:10,450
There's no one else here, just let it out.

736
00:41:12,530 --> 00:41:13,960
Do you two know

737
00:41:15,610 --> 00:41:17,260
what the last sentence my dad wrote to me

738
00:41:17,260 --> 00:41:18,090
was?

739
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:19,360
What?

740
00:41:23,480 --> 00:41:28,180
[My leader must be a jellyfish.
Not only brainless, but also toxic]

741
00:41:28,210 --> 00:41:32,670
[Dad: please delete this...]

742
00:41:29,930 --> 00:41:31,460
I really didn't expect this

743
00:41:32,070 --> 00:41:34,360
to be the last time I talked to my dad.

744
00:41:35,590 --> 00:41:36,400
I thought

745
00:41:38,900 --> 00:41:40,610
I had already moved on.

746
00:41:42,150 --> 00:41:42,690
But...

747
00:41:53,150 --> 00:41:53,670
Dad,

748
00:41:55,740 --> 00:41:57,000
after you passed away,

749
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:59,820
everyone told me that
I just have to accept it

750
00:42:00,220 --> 00:42:01,760
and live a good life,

751
00:42:02,020 --> 00:42:03,730
but I'm really hurting.

752
00:42:05,990 --> 00:42:07,650
How could the last words we said

753
00:42:07,650 --> 00:42:09,260
to each other be these?
